    People also ask
    Quem o pai do cubismo?
    AI Overview
    Pablo Picasso (1881-1973) considerado o pai do cubismo. O artista espanhol foi um pintor, escultor e artista grfico que influenciou a obra de muitos outros artistas. 
    Vida e obra de Picasso
    • Nasceu em Mlaga, na Espanha, em 25 de outubro de 1881 
    • Morreu em Mougins, na Frana, em 8 de abril de 1973 
    • Produziu mais de 45 mil obras, entre pinturas, esculturas, desenhos, gravuras e cermicas 
    • Suas obras mais conhecidas so Les demoiselles d'Avignon, Guernica e Dora Maar au Chat 
    • Recebeu o Prmio Lenin da Paz em 1962 
    Contribuio para o cubismo
    • Em 1907, Picasso e Georges Braque comearam a experimentar com a geometrizao das formas e a apropriao da arte africana 
    • Essas experimentaes estticas deram origem ao cubismo 
    • A obra de Picasso marcou os rumos de uma poca e influenciou a carreira de muitos outros artistas

      Pablo Picasso era brasileiro?
      Ele nasceu no dia 25 de outubro de 1881, em Mlaga, na Espanha. Os pais do artista chamavam-se Mara Picasso Lpez, da qual quase nada se sabe, e Jos Ruiz Blasco, pintor, professor da Escola de Belas Artes de San Telmo e conservador do Museu Municipal. Teve duas irms, Conchita e Lola.

      People also ask
      What is Pablo Picasso's most famous art piece?
      Guernica
      Guernica is a large 1937 oil painting by Spanish artist Pablo Picasso. It is one of his best-known works, regarded by many art critics as the most moving and powerful anti-war painting in history. It is exhibited in the Museo Reina Sofa in Madrid.

      What is Pablo Picasso's artwork called?
      Cubism was one of the most influential styles of the twentieth century. It is generally agreed to have begun around 1907 with Picasso's celebrated painting Demoiselles D'Avignon which included elements of cubist style.

      Cubism - Tate

      Why is Pablo Picasso's art so special?
      He mastered every form of art that he worked with. He never copied anyone. Each style of his work was original. He manipulated his subjects working to create the new style of cubism and his unusual abstract paintings. He truly is in the history of the art world a genius.

      About

      Description

      Pablo Ruiz Picasso was a Spanish painter, sculptor, printmaker, ceramicist, and theatre designer who spent most of his adult life in France. Wikipedia
      Born: October 25, 1881, Mlaga, Spain
      Died: April 8, 1973 (age 91 years), Mougins, France
      Periods: Cubism, Modern art, Surrealism, Picasso's Blue Period See more
      Influenced by: Vincent van Gogh, Paul Czanne See more
      Full name: Pablo Diego Jos Francisco de Paula Juan Nepomuceno Mara de los Remedios Cipriano de la Santsima Trinidad Ruiz y Picasso
      Education: San Fernando Fine Art Royal Academy
